---

<section
  class="exec-section exec-section-auto exec-contrast"
  id="exec-contrast"
>
  <div class="exec-inner">
    <div class="exec-label">The Shift</div>
    <div class="exec-big">
      Every MCO in America runs the same playbook. <span class="hl-coral"
        >Hire more people</span
      > to handle more patients. Here is what that actually looks like.
    </div>

    <div class="contrast-grid">
      <div class="contrast-col contrast-old exec-reveal">
        <div class="contrast-title">How Your MCO Operates Today</div>
        <div class="contrast-item">
          <span class="contrast-icon">&#10005;</span>
          <span
            >Staff manually routes every patient call, SMS, and follow-up.
            Missed touchpoints bleed revenue.</span
          >
        </div>
        <div class="contrast-item">
          <span class="contrast-icon">&#10005;</span>
          <span
            >Coordinators cherry-pick tasks from unmanaged queues. Priority work
            sits while easy tasks get done first.</span
          >
        </div>
        <div class="contrast-item">
          <span class="contrast-icon">&#10005;</span>
          <span
            >Patient profiles go stale between visits. Care gaps surface as
            compliance findings, not as proactive flags.</span
          >
        </div>
        <div class="contrast-item">
          <span class="contrast-icon">&#10005;</span>
          <span
            >Coding happens after the fact. Revenue recovery is reactive. Your
            CFO finds out about undercoding in the quarterly audit.</span
          >
        </div>
        <div class="contrast-item">
          <span class="contrast-icon">&#10005;</span>
          <span
            >Scaling means hiring. Every 500 new patients requires 3–5 new
            coordinators, plus training, plus management overhead.</span
          >
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="contrast-divider">&rarr;</div>

      <div class="contrast-col contrast-new exec-reveal">
        <div class="contrast-title">How It Operates on Machina</div>
        <div class="contrast-item">
          <span class="contrast-icon">&#9889;</span>
          <span
            >AI agents handle routing, follow-up, and escalation across SMS,
            phone, and video. Humans handle judgment calls.</span
          >
        </div>
        <div class="contrast-item">
          <span class="contrast-icon">&#9889;</span>
          <span
            >Intelligent queues auto-prioritize. Agents complete routine tasks
            autonomously. Your team focuses on what requires a human.</span
          >
        </div>
        <div class="contrast-item">
          <span class="contrast-icon">&#9889;</span>
          <span
            >Agentic patient profiles self-update from every interaction.
            Anomalies and care gaps are flagged automatically.</span
          >
        </div>
        <div class="contrast-item">
          <span class="contrast-icon">&#9889;</span>
          <span
            >ACD module codes encounters in real time. Revenue capture is a
            default state, not a recovery project.</span
          >
        </div>
        <div class="contrast-item">
          <span class="contrast-icon">&#9889;</span>
          <span
            >Scaling means configuring, not hiring. Your AI workforce absorbs
            volume. Headcount stays flat. Margins expand.</span
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .exec-contrast {
    background: var(--navy);
    flex-direction: column;
    padding: 120px 40px;
  }

  .contrast-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 60px 1fr;
    gap: 0;
    margin-top: 20px;
    align-items: stretch;
  }

  .contrast-col {
    padding: 40px 36px;
    border-radius: 20px;
  }

  .contrast-old {
    background: linear-gradient(
      145deg,
      rgba(255, 107, 107, 0.04),
      rgba(255, 107, 107, 0.01)
    );
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 107, 107, 0.12);
  }

  .contrast-new {
    background: linear-gradient(
      145deg,
      rgba(240, 180, 41, 0.06),
      rgba(240, 180, 41, 0.01)
    );
    border: 1px solid rgba(240, 180, 41, 0.18);
  }

  .contrast-divider {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    color: var(--gray-500);
  }

  .contrast-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.7rem;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .contrast-old .contrast-title {
    color: var(--coral);
  }

  .contrast-new .contrast-title {
    color: var(--gold);
  }

  .contrast-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 10px;
    padding: 10px 0;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .contrast-old .contrast-item {
    color: var(--gray-300);
  }

  .contrast-new .contrast-item {
    color: var(--gray-100);
  }

  .contrast-icon {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-top: 2px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .contrast-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .contrast-divider {
      transform: rotate(90deg);
      padding: 10px 0;
    }

    .exec-contrast {
      padding: 80px 24px;
    }
  }
</style>
